Experiment No. 7

Aim: To study Control loops in PL/SQL
i.	Sum of first 10 numbers using while loop.
ii.	Sum of first 10 even numbers using for loop.

Solution:

1. Sum of First 10 Numbers Using a WHILE Loop
Procedure Creation:

CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE SumFirst10Numbers_WhileLoop AS
    i NUMBER := 1;
    sum1 NUMBER := 0;
BEGIN
    WHILE i <= 10 LOOP
        sum1 := sum1 + i;
        i := i + 1;
    END LOOP;
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Sum of first 10 numbers using WHILE loop: ' || sum1);
END;
/

2. Sum of First 10 Even Numbers Using a FOR Loop
Procedure Creation:

CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE SumFirst10EvenNumbers_ForLoop AS
    sum1 NUMBER := 0;
BEGIN
    FOR i IN 1..10 LOOP
        sum1 := sum1 + (2 * i);
    END LOOP;
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Sum of first 10 even numbers using FOR loop: ' || sum1);
END;
/


Execution Example:

Call the Procedures in PL/SQL Block:

    BEGIN
        SumFirst10Numbers_WhileLoop;
    END;
    /

    BEGIN
        SumFirst10EvenNumbers_ForLoop;
    END;
    /
Directly in SQLPlus or a similar tool:

EXEC SumFirst10Numbers_WhileLoop;

Outcome:

•	Use WHILE and FOR loops in PL/SQL.
•	Solve repetitive tasks like summing numbers.
•	Handle variables within loops.
•	Differentiate between WHILE and FOR loop mechanics.
•	Display results with DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE.
